> Don't get us wrong, we adore sweet dishes with pineapple (Hello, upside-down cake and piña coladas!). But something magical happens when the fruit is used in savory dishes. Here, we char the pineapple for caramelized notes, then stir into a salsa with tomato, onion, cilantro, and lime. It makes the perfect refreshing-yet-sweet topping for zesty, savory chicken tacos. Dollop over smoky red pepper crema for cooling balance, then take one bite and let the flavor party begin.

Wash and dry all produce.

Dice @Roma tomato{1}(diced). Halve, peel, and thinly slice @red onion{1}(thinly sliced); mince a few slices until you have 2 TBSP (4 TBSP for 4 servings). Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}(roughly chopped). Quarter @lime{1}(quartered). Halve, core, and thinly slice @long green pepper{1}(halved, cored, and thinly sliced) into strips.

Drain @pineapple{4%ounce} and pat dry with #paper towels{}.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tablespoon} in a large #pan{} over medium-high heat. Add pineapple and cook, stirring occasionally, until browned, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Turn off heat and transfer to a small #bowl{}. Wipe out pan.

To bowl with pineapple, add tomato, minced onion, half the cilantro, and lime juice to taste; stir to combine. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for pineapple over medium-high heat. Add green pepper and cook until slightly softened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add sliced onion and cook until veggies are browned and softened, ~{4-5%minutes} more. Season with salt and pepper. Transfer to a #plate{}.

Meanwhile, pat @chicken breast strips{10%ounce} dry with paper towels and season all over with @Southwest spice blend{1%tablespoon}, salt, and pepper.

Once veggies are done, heat a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

While chicken cooks, wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp paper towels; microwave until warm and pliable, ~{30%seconds}.

Divide tortillas between plates and fill with chicken and veggies. Top with pineapple salsa, @smoky red pepper crema{4%tablespoon}, and remaining cilantro. Serve with any remaining lime wedges on the side.